<TITLE> Security heightened around PM's house </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 26 (bdnews24.com)  Security was heightened around the official residence of the prime minister at Hare Road as a stand-off continued at the BDR Headquarters Thursday, more than 24 hours into an armed rebellion by mutinous border guards. "Members of the President's Guard Regiment have been deployed and the residence is surrounded by RAB personnel," a bdnews24.com correspondent said. On the fountain in front of Sheraton Hotel, just off Hare Road, heavy machine guns and 126mm recoilless rifles have been positioned. The correspondent further said a guards regiment jeep is parked horizontally at the gate to the residence of the prime minister. At 3:45pm, small groups with light machine guns have been positioned at certain spots around Hare Road. b
